(528, 1, '2017-08-10 12:57:04', '2017-08-10 12:57:04', '<h3><b>1.0</b> <b>CONCLUSION OF 1</b><b>ST</b><b> SEMESTER 2017 ACTIVITIES</b></h3>\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">The 1</span><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">st</span><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> Semester Exam for NCE, BDP and PGDE/ADE is scheduled to end on the 8</span><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">th</span><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">, 11</span><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">th</span><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">and 19</span><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">th</span><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> of August, 2017 respectively. </span>\n\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">To conclude the Semester, the following were sent earlier:</span>\n<ol>\n 	<li style=\"list-style-type: none;\">\n<ol>\n 	<li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> On 13</span><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">th</span><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> July, 2017, the Academic Records Office sent memo on offline application and registration, and the format for capturing data of the affected students. Equally attached was a specimen of the remita  window for making relevant payments directly through the remita website. </span></li>\n 	<li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> On 23</span><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">rd</span><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> July, the Director Exams sent a standardized format on records of Examination scripts. You were expected to reproduce this form and forward to all examination centers. You were expected to ensure that CDOs and Centre Managers use the form to record the number of scripts at the end of each paper.  You were requested to return the Original Copies of these completed forms to the Director Examinations at the end of the exercise through the Headquarters staff posted to the state.</span></li>\n 	<li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">On 25</span><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">th</span><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> July, the Director FOSS sent a memo titled: 2017 1</span><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">st</span><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> semester exam lists and data on enrolment, registration and attendance for all programmes was sent. The Memo provided format for capturing the list</span> <span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">of students enrolled, registered and that sat for the 1</span><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">st</span><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> semester 2017 examination for all programmes. In the column for “Registered”, you were requested to use the following format: </span>Zone: _______ State: _________ Study Centre: ____________________________________  Session/Year: _________Semester:____ Programme (NCE, PGDE, ADE, or BDP): ___________ Cycle/Level: ________________</li>\n 	<li style=\"font-weight: 400;\">You were expected to prepare separate list for each Programme, Centre, Level/Year respectively using the Class Enrolment/Admission Register, the List of Registered Students and the Attendance List at the Exam for General Courses (such as Education/GSE) should be used to prepare this list. From the list above, you were requested to generate data on admission/enrolment, registration and attendance at 1st semester exam using the attached formats for Forms E1 – E5 for NCE, PGDE, ADE and BDP as at end of 2017 1st Semester Exam. Also, Coordinators were requested to send the updated Forms D1 to D11. <b>You were advised to use Microsoft Excel format as applicable.</b></li>\n 	<li style=\"font-weight: 400;\">It was emphasized that the data submitted should be accurate and submitted by the deadline. All the forms (Forms D1-D11 and E1-E5) and corresponding lists should be sent through NTI headquarters staff sent to states for monitoring and by email not later than 21st August, 2017. Zonal and State Coordinators are to take responsibility for the accuracy and prompt submission of the data requested.</li>\n 	<li style=\"font-weight: 400;\">The Memo of 28th July, 2017 forwarded the PGDE, BDP (300L), NCE 2 &amp; PTTP Teaching Practice Schedule of Activities. While the PGDE, BDP (300L), NCE 2 TP holds for 6 weeks from 2nd Oct to 10th Nov 2017, the PTTP TP holds for 8 weeks from 2nd Oct to 24th Nov 2017. Coordinators were expected to know and communicate to those concerned that only students duly registered before the exercise will and should be supervised.</li>\n 	<li style=\"font-weight: 400;\">On 3rd August, 2017, the ICT Consultant (OmniSwift) report as at 31st July, 2017 was forwarded. Coordinators were expected to download the lists and and extract programme by programme and centre by centre and forward to the centres. They were requested to use the list to tick the column of \"registered by online/portal\" in the format in 1.3 above. Coordinators were advised that “<b>No list of offline admission or offline registration is to be sent to OmniSwift until after the Examinations.</b> States that have sent should re-send the final updated list along with Forms E1 to E5 as well as the Academic Records Offline Registration Templates duly completed.” Coordinators were free to call on the D (FOSS) for clarification if need be.</li>\n</ol>\n</li>\n</ol>\n&nbsp;\n\n&nbsp;\n<h3>2.0 COMMENCEMENT OF 2ND SEMESTER 2017</h3>\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">The 2</span><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">nd</span><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> semester intensive holiday contact session will commence for NCE and BDPs on 22</span><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">nd</span><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> August, 2017, while PGDE and ADE will commence on 2</span><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">nd</span><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> September,2017 nationwide. Do inform all concerned (Centre Desk Officers (CDOs), Centre Managers (CMs), Course Facilitators (CFs), Students and Stakeholders).</span>\n\n&nbsp;\n\n&nbsp;\n<h3>2.1 ACTIVITIES FOR THE DAY OF COMMENCEMENT</h3>\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Centres are to use the day to prepare for a hitch free take-off of the 2</span><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">nd</span><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> Semester. More specifically, the day should be used in documenting all the registered students (fresh and continuing students), issuing available course books, allocating courses to facilitators, perfecting the timetable and familiarising students with the semester’s programme and courses. This may require preparatory meetings between the Centre Managers, CDOs, Course Facilitators and Students.</span>\n\n&nbsp;\n\n&nbsp;\n<h3>2.2 SCHEDULE OF ACTIVITIES FOR THE 2ND SEMESTER</h3>\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">As a reminder, the schedule of activities for the 2</span><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">nd</span><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> semester is attached. Kindly reproduce and circulate to Centres tomorrow. Kindly note the contact days (intensive and weekend are as indicated). As earlier communicated, the BDP tutorial hours for 2017 is 80 hours like the NCE DLS (i.e 20 contacts per semester). As from 2018 session, the approved tutorial hours for BDP shall be 60 hours, i.e 30 hours (15 contacts) per semester. Do communicate this to the Course Facilitators as payment of allowances will be strictly done according to approved tutorial hours as applicable.</span>\n\n<b>3.0 CONCLUSION</b>\n\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">I wish you a successful conclusion of the 2017 1</span><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">st</span><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> semester and smooth commencement of the 2</span><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">nd</span><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> Semester 2017.</span>\n\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Thank you</span>\n\n<strong>Dr. D. O. Yaya</strong>\n\n&nbsp;\n\n<a href=\"https://docs.google.com/document/d/1olzOqZEtRfWbPzRTYDVrHbKuXpviXPLLktWSktGfHg8/edit?usp=sharing\"><strong>Download memo</strong></a>', 'Memo: Conclusion of 1st Semester and Commencement of 2nd Semester 2017 Activities', '', 'draft', 'open', 'open', '', 'memo-conclusion-1st-semester-commencement-2nd-semester-2017-activities', '', '', '2017-08-10 12:57:04', '2017-08-10 12:57:04', '', 0, 'http://52.233.134.86/?p=528', 0, 'post', '', 0),
